Dataset Description:
(max. 75 words)

Our dataset includes numerous statistics about the Covid-19 pandemic in Austria since its beginning. Daily number of infections, hospitalization and deaths are available among different age groups. Moreover, all of the data is aggregatable by states and disctricts. Additionally, the dataset also includes vaccine, test and available hospital beds statistics.

Visualizations¶

Hypothesis 1¶

The number of normal and intensive care hospital beds occupied by patients with COVID-19 and number of deaths of patients with COVID-19 in all Austria decreased overtime as the cumulative number of administered doses of the vaccine against COVID-19 increased.¶

Figure 1: Cumulative number of administered COVID-19 vaccine doses, number of daily deaths and number of occupied normal and intesive care hospital beds until 10.11.2022 (source of data: https://covid19-dashboard.ages.at/).

Hypothesis 2¶

The number of deaths per 100 patients is higher in Vienna compared to Lower Austria among all age groups and all genders.¶

Figure 2: Total number of deaths per 1000 inhabitants in Lower Austria and Vienna until 10.11.2022 by age group and gender (source of data: https://covid19-dashboard.ages.at/).

Description¶

For our first complex hypothesis we used a logarithmic scaling to illustrate the decrease over time. However, that decrease is only clearly visible for the number of daily deaths and the number of occupied intensive beds by Covid-19 patients. Hence we contradict the hyptothesis for the number of occupied normal beds by Covid-19 patients.

We slightly changed the second hypothesis: instead of "number of deaths and hospitalized" (defined in the first submission) we worked with number of deaths only because our dataset is missing information about the gender and age of hospitalized patients. On figure 2 and the interactive visualization (presented in the video "hypothesis_2_video.mov"), the total number of deaths due to COVID-19 per 100 inhabitants was showed for Lower Austria and Vienna per age group and gender. The visualizations confirm the hypothesis that the number of deaths is higher in Vienna compared among all age groups and all genders.

Black vs White Hat Visualization¶

Black Hat Visualization¶

Instructions:

  • Add your black hat visualization
  • Add a description explaining your motivation and design process in producing this visualization (max. 150 words)

Visualization¶

Description¶

The plot shows the death count and the number of residents by age group. We used a logaritmich scale and the axes are inverted so that it appears at the first glance that the number of deaths was very high, for example for the >84 age group it seems that 3/4 of the people died.

White Hat Visualization¶

Instructions:

  • Add your white hat visualization

Visualization¶

Description¶

Plot shows number of Covid-19 infections aggregated by month. Line histogram was used as the data is a ditribution with many data points.The data was grouped by month to make it more legible. The y-axis grid, bi-annual time ticks and thousands separators were used to make the plot easier to read. (source of data: https://covid19-dashboard.ages.at/).
